/a> for supporting our science!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1024\" height=\"511\" src=\"http:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/europetocaltech-1-1024x511.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3955\" srcset=\"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/europetocaltech-1-1024x511.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/europetocaltech-1-300x150.jpg 300w, https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/europetocaltech-1-768x383.jpg 768w, https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/europetocaltech-1-1536x766.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/01\/europetocaltech-1-2048x1022.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" \/><\/figure>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The COST action GWverse is an impressive network of European researchers and institutions tackling gravitational waves, black holes, etc (i.e. the things I like&#8230; sweet!). Together with conferences and outreach, they support collaborative visits between the network members, so here &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/2019\/01\/07\/cost-visitors-come-to-california\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_coblocks_attr":"","_coblocks_dimensions":"","_coblocks_responsive_height":"","_coblocks_accordion_ie_support":"","_mi_skip_tracking":false,"spay_email":""},"categories":[4,6,16],"tags":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","amp_validity":null,"amp_enabled":true,"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2391"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/davidegerosa.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embedd